-p , --play

Play a set of audio files. While playing, pressing space pauses play,
pressing space again resumes it. Moving backward and forward is done with
b (6 seconds back), capital B (60 seconds back), less-than (600 seconds
back), left-bracket (back to the start), or with f (six seconds forward),
capital F (60 seconds forward), greater-than (600 seconds forward),
or right-bracket (6 seconds before the end).  If a number of files is
being played, pressing n moves to the next item in the list, pressing
p moves to the previous item, and pressing q stops play and exits.
A bookmark is saved so that an interrupted file can be resumed where
it was interrupted.  During play, or while paused, pressing the comma
reports file position in minutes and seconds, pressing period reports
it as the percent of the file already played.
